CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 29, 1969, pg. 15, reads: "YOUNG AND OLD ALIKE were among the throng attending the Palmer Hayden exhibit as can be seen here. Among the artists were J. Brooks Dendy III, originator of the Creata-Drama at Carnegie Institute and his wife, singer-actress Brenda Joyce Jackson, and sculptor Thaddeus Moseley [sic] (holding his child0 and his wife.  The Moseleys feel it is never too early to make a child aware of the finer things in life."
TitMainTitle: J. Brooks Dendy III, Brenda Joyce Jackson, Thaddeus "Thad" Mosley holding his baby Tereneh, and Yvonne Reed Mosley, standing near painting titled "John Henry Was the Best in the Land" at Palmer Hayden exhibition in University Art Gallery, Frick Fine Arts Building, University of Pittsburgh
